d macOS. Still, applications like TeamViewer and LogMeIn make it much easier to provide a range of different session functionalities. And if you’re an educator, since educational institutions have also gone ‘online’, you can update your students through your scheduling app. In that case, your students can view your timetable and meet you at a particular time according to that. E-mails, mentions on Facebook, notifications of messaging apps are a constant distraction for a working person. Notifications such as these bombard workers the minute they sign in. Employees use applications such as Freedom and FocusMe to restrict alerts for some time to reduce distractions so that they can remain concentrated and efficient on the task at hand. Back-end enterprises are using advanced technology systems to make it easier for workers to make their everyday lives more comfortable. But if your company or institute is not providing the facility, there are ways for you to do it yourself by installing applications supporting these functions. Most organizations use project management software since the beginning because it helps them stay focused. However, this year was a bit different. Now, the software carries on vast degrees of purpose as staff continues to work from home. Without the freedom to periodically update the details in person, project management software can easily keep your team on top of numerous plans and items. Ensure everything you are concentrating on is explicitly defined on your host location, whether you use Calendly, Asana, Trello, or anything else. Teamwork project management software recommends setting up a strategic project plan for your job early on, so things don’t go off track later in the process. It will ease the strain on needless meetings by offering feedback on how your tasks are going along and inspiring your colleagues to do the same. Every year the demand for digital assistants increases by upwards of 50 percent, and there’s a decent possibility that there’s one in your house already. Many employees are now very comfortable with digital assistants, whether it’s an Amazon Echo, a Google Assistant, or a Siri-enabled Apple product. But very few are leveraging the digital help to their max potential for work currently. You can make phone calls, send an e-mail, write notes, and do much more with digital assistants. Although it may usually be distracting to use one in the workplace, using one at home may allow people to work as they cook, clean, or execute other essential household tasks. Without any of the complicated teamwork you need, some digital assistants may even help you conduct conference calls. As employees go home, this rapid shift to working remotely around the country may also be named “the Zoom boom.” Among the most successful video calling sites on the web, Zoom is estimated to produce substantial progress. Face-to-face sessions are the foundation of many companies; it is not an option to remove them entirely. Since Covid19, platforms such as Zoom, Skype, and Google Hangouts benefit institutes from contacting colleagues or customers from a distance. Although video chats may not have the same atmosphere as in-person presentations, they provide an efficient substitute in cases like ours. There are distractions in both kinds of work that employees do. There are colleagues and unnecessary meetings in the physical office that you can’t even put to stop. Whereas working online is better with these tech tools. Working from home was a phenomenon before the pandemic too, it is not that bad. Employees have reported being 13.5% more productive and efficient than their colleagues while they work from home. So enjoy it until you have the chance and see if you are feeling the same. For most people, food clothes and shelter are most priorities of life. You worry about these things because their absence dehumanizes a being and denigrates standard living. But for those, particularly, living in Lagos metropolis, these, are ironically, not far fetched. No matter how poor, in Lagos, one must feed.… December 11, 2014 In "Technology" RECENTLY a team of Nigerian app developers, Marvel Web, hoisted Nigeria’s flag in Sweden by emerging winners in a world app contest instituted by renowned telecom equipment manufacturers, Ericsson. Hi-Tech, recently cornered one of the leaders of the team Mr Toks Ogun, who gave us insight into the preparatory and… June 25, 2014 In "Technology" The global software giant, Microsoft has announced the availability of Office 2013 in Nigeria, the next iteration of the company’s flagship Office product line for consumers. March 22, 2013 In "Technology"